[thinking] **Considering annotation implications**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm reflecting on the "Do not create source stubs" package-private annotation. It might be viewed as more of a test support than a library API, which is acceptable but could be seen as unnecessary. I wonder if we should use Deprecated.class instead to avoid extra complexity. The issue arises with top-level classes being public; the annotation isn’t tied to test classes. Also, there's a potential issue with how package-private annotations might be handled in Native Image regarding class removal and metadata generation. It’s quite complex!
[thinking] 
